# ui-shadcn Component Usage

## Golden Rule

**`className` is NOT a valid prop. Use variants and props only.**

## Quick Reference

```tsx
// ❌ Will NOT compile - className removed from all components
<Button className="bg-red-500">Delete</Button>
<Card className="shadow-xl">Content</Card>

// ✅ GOOD - use variants and props
<Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
<Card maxWidth="lg">Content</Card>
```

## Layout Positioning

Use wrapper elements for layout concerns:

```tsx
// ✅ Wrapper for width
<div className="w-full">
  <Button>Full Width</Button>
</div>

// ✅ Use Stack/Grid for spacing
<Stack gap="4">
  <Button>First</Button>
  <Button>Second</Button>
</Stack>
```

## Common Components

| Component | Key Props |
|-----------|-----------|
| `Button` | `variant`, `size`, `loading`, `iconLeft`, `iconRight` |
| `Card` | `maxWidth` (sm/md/lg/xl/2xl/3xl/full) |
| `Stack` | `direction`, `gap`, `align`, `justify` |
| `Heading` | `level` (1-6), `variant` |
| `Text` | `size`, `variant`, `weight` |
| `Badge` | `variant` |
| `PageLayout` | `variant` (default/center), `padding` |

## Missing a variant?

Add it to the component's `cva` definition. Never use wrapper divs to apply what should be component styling.
